{
  "texts": [
    "For x, x ′ ∈ 2 <ω, let x ′ ⊑ x iff x ′ extends x, i.e., x is an initial segment of x ′.",
    "We can view ⟨2 <ω, ⊑⟩ as the infinite complete binary tree with ⊑ as the reflexive transitive closure of the child relation-a simple example of a possibility space in which every possibility can be further refined.",
    "Observe that for each x ∈ 2 <ω, ↓x satisfies refinability and hence ↓x ∈ RO(2 <ω, ⊑), so RO(2 <ω, ⊑) is an atomless Boolean algebra.",
    "As an exercise, consider various definitions of accessibility relations on ⟨2 <ω, ⊑⟩ and then check which, if any, of the interplay conditions are satisfied.",
    "For example, for n ∈ N, define an accessibility relation R n by: xR n y iff x and y have the same length and differ in no more than n places, i.e., where x = ⟨x 1,..., x k ⟩ and y = ⟨y 1,..., y k ⟩, 2.11 for R 1."
  ]
}